    <section class="py-16 bg-slate-50">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
          <h2 class="uppercase text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-8 text-center">Interior vs Exterior FAQ</h2>
          
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div class="bg-white  overflow-hidden border-2 border-slate-600">
              <button class="w-full text-left p-6 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-yellow-500" data-faq-toggle>
                <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
                  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">Which system lasts longer - interior or exterior?</h3>
                  <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-cyan-400 transition-transform duration-200" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
                  </svg>
                </div>
              </button>
              <div class="hidden px-6 pb-6">
                <p class="text-slate-600">
                  Exterior systems typically last 25-30+ years with minimal maintenance, while interior systems last 15-25 years but require periodic sump pump maintenance. However, interior systems are easier and less expensive to upgrade or repair when needed, and modern pumps are very reliable with proper maintenance.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white  overflow-hidden border-2 border-slate-600">
              <button class="w-full text-left p-6 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-yellow-500" data-faq-toggle>
                <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
                  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">Can I install an interior system if I have finished basement?</h3>
                  <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-cyan-400 transition-transform duration-200" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
                  </svg>
                </div>
              </button>
              <div class="hidden px-6 pb-6">
                <p class="text-slate-600">
                  Yes, interior systems can be installed in finished basements, but it requires removing flooring along the perimeter and potentially some wall sections. Professional installers can minimize disruption and restore finishes, though this adds to the project cost. Many homeowners use this as an opportunity to upgrade their basement finishes.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white  overflow-hidden border-2 border-slate-600">
              <button class="w-full text-left p-6 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-yellow-500" data-faq-toggle>
                <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
                  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">Which system works better in Toronto's clay soil?</h3>
                  <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-cyan-400 transition-transform duration-200" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
                  </svg>
                </div>
              </button>
              <div class="hidden px-6 pb-6">
                <p class="text-slate-600">
                  Interior systems often work better in Toronto's clay soil because they manage hydrostatic pressure rather than fighting it. Clay soil's poor drainage creates high pressure that can overwhelm exterior membranes over time. Interior systems capture and redirect this pressure effectively, which is why they're the preferred solution for most Toronto contractors.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white  overflow-hidden border-2 border-slate-600">
              <button class="w-full text-left p-6 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-yellow-500" data-faq-toggle>
                <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
                  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">Should I get both interior and exterior systems?</h3>
                  <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-cyan-400 transition-transform duration-200" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
                  </svg>
                </div>
              </button>
              <div class="hidden px-6 pb-6">
                <p class="text-slate-600">
                  Combined systems offer maximum protection but are expensive ($35,000-$50,000+). They're justified for high-value properties, severe problems, or critical basement uses. For most Toronto homes, a properly installed interior system provides excellent protection at much lower cost. Consider exterior systems when doing major renovations or if interior solutions haven't been effective.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white  overflow-hidden border-2 border-slate-600">
